('1454','small molecule','3,4-Methylenedioxyme','An N-substituted amphetamine analog. It is a widely abused drug classified as a hallucinogen and causes marked, long-lasting changes in brain serotonergic systems. It is commonly referred to as MDMA or ecstasy. [PubChem] ','MDMA acts as a releasing agent of serotonin, norepinephrine, and dopamine.',''),
