('1486','small molecule','Cathine','Cathine (β-hydroxyamphetamine) is a monoamine alkaloid found in the shrub Catha edulis (khat). Cathine is a Schedule III drug under the Convention on Psychotropic Substances. In the United States, it is classified as a Schedule IV controlled substance. [Wikipedia]','Closely related to ephedrine, cathinone and other amphetamines, it may contribute to the stimulant effect of <i>Catha edulis</i>, although another constituent, cathinone appears to show stronger activity.',''),
