('1520','small molecule','Tenocyclidine','Tenocyclidine (TCP, thienyl cyclohexylpiperidine) is a dissociative anesthetic drug with stimulant and hallucinogenic effects. It is similar in effects to phencyclidine but is considerably more potent. Due to its similarity in effects to PCP, TCP was placed into the Schedule I list of illegal drugs in the 1970s, although it was only briefly abused in the 1970s and 1980s and is now little known. [Wikipedia]','Tenocyclidine (TCP) has slightly different binding properties to phencyclidine (PCP), with more affinity for NMDA receptors but less affinity for sigma receptors.',''),
